remarks.format:
  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-102">Paski lub pasków, są poziomy lub pionowy zakresy, które cieniowanie tło wykresu w odstępach czasu z regularnych lub niestandardowych.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-102">Strip lines, or strips, are horizontal or vertical ranges that shade the background of a chart in regular or custom intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-103">Możesz użyć paska linii:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-103">You can use strip lines to:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-104">Poprawa czytelności do wyszukiwania poszczególne wartości na wykresie.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-104">Improve readability for looking up individual values on the chart.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-105">Poszczególne punkty danych podczas odczytywania wykresu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-105">Separate data points when reading the chart.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-106">Wyróżnij dat, które w regularnych odstępach czasu, na przykład można zidentyfikować dane, weekendy punktów.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-106">Highlight dates that occur at regular intervals, for example, to identify weekend data points.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-107">Wyróżnij kluczowe określony zakres danych.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-107">Highlight a specific key range of data.</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-108">Dodaj wiersz próg w określonej wartości stałej.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-108">Add a threshold line at a specific constant value.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-109">Pojedynczy <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> obiektu można albo wyciągnąć wielokrotnie, lub jeden raz dla danego interwału.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-109">A single <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> object can either be drawn once, or repeatedly, for a given interval.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-110">Ta akcja jest kontrolowana przez <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> właściwości.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-110">This action is controlled by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-111">Gdy wartość -1 jest przypisany do <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> właściwość, Usuń jeden wiersz będą pobierane.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-111">When a value of -1 is assigned to the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property, one strip line will be drawn.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-112">Gdy wartość niezerową jest przypisany do <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> właściwości pasek będą rysowane wielokrotnie w każdym danego interwału.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-112">When a non-zero value is assigned to the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Interval%2A> property, a strip line will be drawn repeatedly at each given interval.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-113">Lokalizacja, gdzie jest rysowany pasek wpływa także <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffset%2A> i <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffsetType%2A> właściwości linii paska.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-113">The location where a strip line is drawn is also affected by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffset%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.IntervalOffsetType%2A> properties of the strip line.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-114">Paski zawsze są skojarzone z <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Axis> obiektu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-114">Strip lines are always associated with an <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.Axis> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-115">One można dodawać w czasie projektowania i w czasie wykonywania.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-115">They can be added at both design time and run time.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-116">Aby dodać linii poziomej lub pionowej, aby wyświetlić wartości progowej, ustaw <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> właściwości na wartość 0,0.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-116">To add a horizontal or vertical line to display a threshold, set the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property to a value of 0.0.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-117">Spowoduje to linii.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-117">This will result in a line being drawn.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-118">Możesz użyć <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderDashStyle%2A> i <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderWidth%2A> właściwości kolor, szerokość i styl linii.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-118">You can use the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A>, <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderDashStyle%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderWidth%2A> properties for the color, width and style of the line.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-119">Nie właściwości tła wykresu (`Back*`) są używane podczas <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> właściwość ma wartość 0,0.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-119">No chart background properties (`Back*`) are used when the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property is set to 0.0.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-120">Użyj <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Text%2A> właściwości paska linii, aby skojarzyć tekst z paska linii.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-120">Use the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.Text%2A> property of the strip line to associate text with a strip line.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-121">Położenie i orientację ten tekst może być kontrolowane przez <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.TextAlignment%2A> właściwości.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-121">The placement and orientation of this text can be controlled by the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.TextAlignment%2A> property.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-122">Wiele wierszy taśmy są zdefiniowane dla tej samej osi, jest to możliwe, że paski będzie nakładają się na siebie.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-122">When multiple strip lines are defined for the same axis, it is possible that the strip lines will overlap.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-123">Porządek osi z <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> obiektów zależy od kolejności ich występowania na <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLinesCollection> obiektu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-123">The Z-order of <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine> objects is determined by their order of occurrence in the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLinesCollection> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-124">Oznacza to, że pierwsze wystąpienie jest rysowane jako pierwsze; drugie wystąpienie jest rysowana po drugie, i tak dalej.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-124">This means that the first occurrence is drawn first; the second occurrence is drawn second, and so on.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-125">Paski nie są obsługiwane dla następujących typów wykresu: Kołowy, pierścieniowy, lejka, ostrosłupowy Kagi, przebicia trzech linii, punktowo-kształtowego, Polar i radarowego.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-125">Strip lines are not supported for the following chart types: Pie, Doughnut, Funnel, Pyramid, Kagi, ThreeLineBreak, PointAndFigure, Polar and Radar.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-126">Poniższy przykład kodu pokazuje trzy aplikacje pasków.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-126">The following code example demonstrates three applications of strip lines.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-127">Po pierwsze, poziome paski są dodawane w interwałach cyklicznych.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-127">First, horizontal strip lines are added at recurring intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-128">Drugi, pionowe paski są dodawane do wyróżniania danych weekend punktów.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-128">Second, vertical strip lines are added to highlight weekend data points.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-129">Na koniec niepowtarzalnych paska linii jest dodawany do oznaczania średniej punktów danych w pierwszej serii wykresu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-129">Lastly, a non-recurring strip line is added to denote the mean of the data points in the first series of the chart.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Imports System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting  
  
Public Partial Class StripLines   
    Inherits System.Web.UI.Page   
    Protected Sub Page_Load(ByVal sender As Object, ByVal e As EventArgs)  
  
        ' Add chart data before adding strip lines.   
        AddChartData()   
  
        ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.   
        AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
  
        ' Highlights weekend points using strip lines.   
        HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
  
        ' Adds a threshold line using strip lines.   
        AddThresholdStripLine()   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.   
    Private Sub AddChartData()   
        ' Declare new random variable   
        Dim rand As New Random()   
        For i As Integer = 0 To 6   
  
            ' Add a week of data   
            chart1.Series(0).Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.[Next](20, 35))   
        Next   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.   
    Private Sub AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
        ' Instantiate new strip line   
        Dim stripLine1 As New StripLine()  
        stripLine1.StripWidth = 2.5   
        stripLine1.Interval = 5   
  
        ' Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter   
        stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red)   
  
        ' Add the strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1)   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.   
    Private Sub HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
        ' Set strip line to highlight weekends   
        Dim stripLine2 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold)   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5   
        stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
        stripLine2.Interval = 1   
        stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks   
        stripLine2.StripWidth = 2   
        stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2)   
  
        ' Set the axis label to show the name of the day   
        ' This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd"   
    End Sub   
  
    ' Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the mean value of the first series.  
    Private Sub AddThresholdStripLine()   
        Dim stripLine3 As New StripLine()   
  
        ' Set threshold line so that it is only shown once   
        stripLine3.Interval = 0   
  
        ' Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series   
        stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series(0).Name)   
  
        stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen   
        stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25   
  
        ' Set text properties for the threshold line   
        stripLine3.Text = "Mean"   
        stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black   
  
        ' Add strip line to the chart   
        chart1.ChartAreas(0).AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3)   
    End Sub   
End Class  
```  
  
```csharp  
public partial class StripLines : System.Web.UI.Page   
    {  
        protected void Page_Load(object sender, EventArgs e)  
        {              
            // Add chart data  
            AddChartData();  
  
            // Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.  
            AddHorizRepeatingStripLines();  
  
            // Highlights weekend points using strip lines.  
            HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines();  
  
            // Adds a threshold line using strip lines.  
            AddThresholdStripLine();  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddChartData()  
        {  
            // Declare new random variable  
            Random rand = new Random();  
  
            // Add a week of data  
            for (int i = 0; i < 7; i++)   
            {  
                chart1.Series[0].Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.Next(20,35));  
            }  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()  
        {  
            // Instantiate new strip line  
            StripLine stripLine1 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine1.StripWidth = 0;  
            stripLine1.BorderColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BorderWidth = 3;  
            stripLine1.Interval = 5;  
  
            // Consider adding transparency so that the strip lines are lighter  
            stripLine1.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Red);  
  
            stripLine1.BackSecondaryColor = Color.Black;  
            stripLine1.BackGradientStyle = GradientStyle.LeftRight;  
  
            // Add the strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine1);  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds strip lines to highlight weekend values.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()  
        {  
            // Set strip line to highlight weekends  
            StripLine stripLine2 = new StripLine();  
            stripLine2.BackColor = Color.FromArgb(120, Color.Gold);              
            stripLine2.IntervalOffset = -1.5;  
            stripLine2.IntervalOffsetType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
            stripLine2.Interval = 1;  
            stripLine2.IntervalType = DateTimeIntervalType.Weeks;  
            stripLine2.StripWidth = 2;  
            stripLine2.StripWidthType = DateTimeIntervalType.Days;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.StripLines.Add(stripLine2);  
  
            // Set the axis label to show the name of the day  
            // This is done in order to demonstrate that weekends are highlighted  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisX.LabelStyle.Format = "ddd";  
        }  
  
        /// <summary>  
        /// Adds a horizontal threshold strip line at the calculated mean   
        /// value of all data points in the first series of the chart.  
        /// </summary>  
        private void AddThresholdStripLine()  
        {  
            StripLine stripLine3 = new StripLine();  
  
            // Set threshold line so that it is only shown once  
            stripLine3.Interval = 0;  
  
            // Set the threshold line to be drawn at the calculated mean of the first series  
            stripLine3.IntervalOffset = chart1.DataManipulator.Statistics.Mean(chart1.Series[0].Name);  
  
            stripLine3.BackColor = Color.DarkGreen;  
            stripLine3.StripWidth = 0.25;  
  
            // Set text properties for the threshold line  
            stripLine3.Text = "Mean";  
            stripLine3.ForeColor = Color.Black;  
  
            // Add strip line to the chart  
            chart1.ChartAreas[0].AxisY.StripLines.Add(stripLine3);  
        }  
    }  
```

  
  
## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-134">Tę właściwość można ustawić na dowolną prawidłową wartość ARGB (alpha, czerwony, zielony, niebieski).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-134">You can set this property to any valid ARGB (alpha, red, green, blue) value.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-135">Gradient do paska linii ustawia <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackColor%2A> i <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackSecondaryColor%2A> właściwości.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-135">To set a gradient for the strip line, set the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackColor%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BackSecondaryColor%2A> properties.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-136">Jeśli ustawisz ten kolor na "przezroczyste" — innymi słowy, ustaw wartość alfa 0 - Brak koloru zostanie przypisany do tła elementu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-136">If you set this color to "transparent" - in other words, set the alpha value to 0 - no color will be assigned to the background of the element.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-137">W rezultacie tła ma być przezroczysty.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-137">As a result, the background will be transparent.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-138">Jeśli <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> właściwość ma wartość 0,0, będą rysowane linię i <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A> właściwość określi kolor linii, a nie w tej właściwości.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-138">If the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.StripWidth%2A> property is set to 0.0, a line will be drawn and the <xref:System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting.StripLine.BorderColor%2A> property will determine the color of the line, not this property.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-139">Poniższy przykład kodu pokazuje trzy aplikacje pasków.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-139">The following code example demonstrates three applications of strip lines.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-140">Po pierwsze, poziome paski są dodawane w interwałach cyklicznych.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-140">First, horizontal strip lines are added at recurring intervals.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-141">Drugi, pionowe paski są dodawane do wyróżniania danych weekend punktów.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-141">Second, vertical strip lines are added to highlight weekend data points.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c4bbe-142">Na koniec niepowtarzalnych paska linii jest dodawany do oznaczania średniej punktów danych w pierwszej serii wykresu.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c4bbe-142">Lastly, a non-recurring strip line is added to denote the mean of the data points in the first series of the chart.</span></span>  
  
```vb  
Imports System.Web.UI.DataVisualization.Charting  
  
Public Partial Class StripLines   
    Inherits System.Web.UI.Page   
    Protected Sub Page_Load(ByVal sender As Object, ByVal e As EventArgs)  
  
        ' Add chart data before adding strip lines.   
        AddChartData()   
  
        ' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines.   
        AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
  
        ' Highlights weekend points using strip lines.   
        HighlightWeekendsWithStripLines()   
  
        ' Adds a threshold line using strip lines.   
        AddThresholdStripLine()   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds a week of data with values between 20 and 35.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddChartData()   
        ' Declare new random variable   
        Dim rand As New Random()   
        For i As Integer = 0 To 6   
  
            ' Add a week of data   
            chart1.Series(0).Points.AddXY(DateTime.Now.AddDays(i), rand.[Next](20, 35))   
        Next   
    End Sub   
  
    ''' <summary>   
    ''' Adds repeating horizontal strip lines at intervals of 5.   
    ''' </summary>   
    Private Sub AddHorizRepeatingStripLines()   
        ' Instantiate new strip line   
        Dim stripLine1 As New StripLine()   
        stripLine1.StripWidth = 2.5   
        stripLine1.Interval = 5   
  
